node.text: The living legend @MikeHornExplorer tells us about the horrible scenes he has witnessed during his adventures and the importance of the young generations in the race to save our planet ! We must all get together now and start moving, it’s time for action ! Our special thanks to @spgrytz for supporting our vision towards a sustainable environment! #DiscoverEarth

node.text:
10 Architectural Marvels to visit in Iran✨ Which photo is your favorite, from 1 to 10?

Make sure to save this post for your next trip! 📝

1. Imam Reza Holy Shrine
2. Nasir al Molk Mosque
3. Mollabashi Historical House
4. Hazrat Masumeh Holy Shrine
5. Nasir al Molk Mosque
6. National Arts Museum, Tehran
7. Shah Mosque
8. Sadoughi House Yazd
9. Jameh Mosque of Shafei
10. Borujerdiha Historical House

🇮🇷 #discoverIran with @amir.hossesin.mirmoeini

node.text:
Overgrown haven in the heart of Bali 🌿 Would you spend the day on the poolside of this stunning villa?

Whenever we’re talking about Bali, we have to mention its stunning nature. Diving, hiking, enjoying waterfalls and touring temples…the opportunities of this paradise are endless ☀️

📍Bali, Indonesia

🇮🇩 #discoverIndonesia with @daniel.koh

node.text:
A secluded forest retreat 🌲 Tag a friend who’d love this A-frame cabin!

If you’re looking for the most amazing forest trails, Utah is a great go-to. Forests cover 1/3 of the state, disrupted by lakes and mountains for an even better time ⛰️

📍Utah, United States

🇺🇸 #discoverUnitedStates with @malakyunus

node.text:
Bath time with a view 🛁 Would you try this bath session?

You can find this special experience in Fribourg, a Swiss city with a historical charm. If you decide to spend a day or two in the town, don’t forget to visit the St-Nicolas Cathedral and the Museum of Art and History 🎨

📍 Fribourg, Switzerland 

🇨🇭 #discoverSwitzerland with @felixunholz

node.text:
Have you ever seen clouds like this? ☁️ These cellular patterned clouds are called mammatus clouds. They are definitely some of the most distinct clouds, resembling little pouches emerging from the base of the cloud.

Would you visit Santiago?

node.text:
Have you heard about the Shelf Clouds seen earlier this week in Georgia? ☁️

Shelf and roll clouds are types of arcus clouds, and are known to have the shape of a long bar or shelf below a storm cloud. Have you ever seen them before?

📍 Commerce, Georgia, United States

🇺🇸 #discoverUnitedStates
video by Jaymi Knight
